"'''Judge's Call'''" is a short story written by [[Timothy Zahn]] for [[Wikipedia:Valentine's Day|Valentine's Day]] of [[2004]] and was made available for free online at the [[Del Rey]] website. It is set [[21 ABY/Legends|21 ABY]] and details the second honeymoon of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]].

==Plot summary==
[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and his wife [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara]] are on a [[Planet/Legends|planet]], where Luke is helping to arbitrate many disputes among the natives, who revere [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] wisdom. Mara grows increasingly frustrated at the amount of Luke's time being taken by settling these disputes. On a visit to [[Kei Ras Cirali]], an agricultural coordinator, Luke takes Mara to a remote retreat that he has had furnished with things she likes so they can spend some time together alone.

